"Bel L., Bar-Hen A., Petit R., Cheddadi R.","Spatio-temporal functional regression on paleoecological data",2011,"Journal of Applied Statistics","38","4",,"695","704",,,10.1080/02664760903563650,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79551713734&partnerID=40&md5=2dca2e05084735767542a93dc517f5f8","UMR MIA-518 Agro Paris Tech-INRA, 16 rue Claude Bernard - 75231, Paris Cedex 05, France; Université René Descartes, MAP5, 45 rue des Saints Pères, 75270 Paris Cedex 06, France; UMR 1202 INRA, 69 route d'Arcachon, 33612 Cestas Cedex, France; ISEM, CNRS UMR 5554, Case Postale 61, 34095 Montpellier, France","Bel, L., UMR MIA-518 Agro Paris Tech-INRA, 16 rue Claude Bernard - 75231, Paris Cedex 05, France; Bar-Hen, A., Université René Descartes, MAP5, 45 rue des Saints Pères, 75270 Paris Cedex 06, France; Petit, R., UMR 1202 INRA, 69 route d'Arcachon, 33612 Cestas Cedex, France; Cheddadi, R., ISEM, CNRS UMR 5554, Case Postale 61, 34095 Montpellier, France","There is much interest in predicting the impact of global warming on the genetic diversity of natural populations and the influence of climate on biodiversity is an important ecological question. Since Holocene, we face many climate perturbations and the geographical ranges of plant taxa have changed substantially. Actual genetic diversity of plant is a result of these processes and a first step to study the impact of future climate change is to understand the important features of reconstructed climate variables such as temperature or precipitation for the last 15,000 years on actual genetic diversity of forest. We model the relationship between genetic diversity in the European beech (Fagus sylvatica) forests and curves of temperature and precipitation reconstructed from pollen databases. Our model links the genetic measureto the climate curves. We adapt classical functional linear model to take into account interactions between climate variables as a bilinear form. Since the data are georeferenced, our extensions also account for the spatial dependence among the observations. The practical issues of these methodological extensions are discussed. © 2011 Taylor & Francis.","Biodiversity; Climate change; Functional data analysis; Spatial regression; Spatio-temporal modeling",,,,,,,"Cardot, H., Ferraty, F., Sarda, P., Functional linear model (1999) Stat. Probab. Lett, 45, pp. 11-22; Cheddadi, R., Bar-Hen, A., Spatial gradient of temperature and potential vegetation feedback across Europe during the late Quaternary (2009) Clim. Dynam, 32 (2-3), pp. 371-379; Comps, B., Gömöry, D., Letouzey, J., Thiébaut, B., Petit, R.J., Diverging trends between heterozygosity and allelic richness during postglacial colonization in the European beech (2001) Genetics, 157, pp. 389-397; Cressie, N., (1993) Statistics for Spatial Data, , revised ed., Wiley, NewYork; Dahl-Jensen, D., Mosegaard, K., Gundestrup, N., Clow, G.D., Johnsen, S.J., Hansen, A.W., Balling, N., Past temperatures directly from the Greenland Ice Sheet (1998) Science, 282, pp. 268-271; Fan, J., Zhang, J.T., Two-step estimation of functional linear models with application to longitudinal data (2000) J. R. Stat. Soc. Ser. B Stat. Methodol, 62, pp. 303-322; Faraway, J.J., Regression analysis for a functional response (1997) Technometrics, 39, pp. 254-261; Guiot, J., Methodology of the last climatic cycle reconstruction in France from pollen data (1990) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol, 80, pp. 49-69; Guyon, X., (2001) Statistique Et Économétrie, , Ellipses Marketing, Paris; Müller, H.G., Stadtmüller, U., Generalized functional linear models (2005) Ann. Stat, 33, pp. 774-806; Prentice, C.I., Guiot, J., Huntley, B., Jolly, D., Cheddadi, R., Reconstructing biomes from palaeocological data: A general method and its application to European pollen data at 0 and 6 ka (1996) Clim. Dyn, 12, pp. 185-194; Ramsay, J.O., Silverman, B.W., (1997) Functional Data Analysis, , Springer, NewYork; Seierstad, J., Nesje, A., Dahl, S.O., Simonsen, J.R., (2002) Holocene glacier fluctuations of Grovabreen and Holocene snow-avalanche activity reconstructed from lake sediments in Groningstolsvatnet, western Norway, 12 (2), pp. 211-222. , The Holocene","Bel, L.; UMR MIA-518 Agro Paris Tech-INRA, 16 rue Claude Bernard - 75231, Paris Cedex 05, France; email: liliane.bel@agroparistech.fr",,,,,,,,02664763,,,,"English","J. Appl. Stat.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-79551713734
